{
  "texts": [
    "Let F be a partial-state frame F = ⟨S, ⊑, {R i } i∈I, P ⟩.1.",
    "F is R-tight iff for all i ∈ I and x, y ∈ S, if ∀Z ∈ P, x ∈ ■ i Z ⇒ y ∈ Z, then xR i y; 2.",
    "F is ⊑-tight iff for all x, y ∈ S, if ∀Z ∈ P, x ∈ Z ⇒ y ∈ Z, then y ⊑ x; 3.",
    "F is tight iff it is R-tight and ⊑-tight.",
    "◁Note that for any partial-state frame,xR i y implies ∀Z ∈ P, x ∈ ■ i Z ⇒ y ∈ Z;and for any possibility frame, y ⊑ x implies ∀Z ∈ P, x ∈ Z ⇒ y ∈ Z."
  ]
}